      <data key="d0">VENTILATION STRATEGIES</data>
      <data key="d1">ENGINEERING_CONTROL</data>
      <data key="d2">Engineering/operational modifications to ventilation and airflow patterns intended to reduce airborne contaminant dispersion in indoor healthcare environments (e.g., ward ventilation configurations assessed via modeling). | Alternative ventilation configurations/operating modes evaluated as an engineering control to influence indoor air mixing/removal, affecting CO2 accumulation and cough-generated droplet dispersion in enclosed spaces (e.g., a hospital lift). Specific rates/technologies are not provided in the excerpt.</data>
